# bench/ publishes the benchmark *method* for OSS transparency — the runbook (perf/run-perf.sh),
# the k6 scenarios, the python drivers, the Grafana provisioning, and docker-compose.yml.
#
# It never publishes the raw run artifacts, which carry local paths / machine details and are large
# + regenerable. The curated numbers live in performance/ (CSVs + README). Keep these out of git:

# Any locally-cached generator binary (run-perf.sh uses k6 on PATH + oha from ~/.cargo/bin; nothing
# is fetched into bench/, but ignore a /bin/ if one is created manually).
/bin/

# Raw run outputs: HTML reports + text logs contain absolute local paths (/home/<user>/…), and JSON
# summaries are regenerable working data. Proxy startup logs echo demo keys + local detail.
/results/
/results-wasm/

# Local results write-up with machine specs; the public report is performance/README.md.
/RESULTS.md

# Belt-and-suspenders: never commit these regardless of where they land under bench/.
*.html
*.log
*.tar.gz
